    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Irregularly shaped and uneven gold or silver coins struck in various parts of the Spanish Empire between the 16th and 18th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000012271/Doty, Macmillan Encyclopedic Dictionary of Numismatics (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Monedas de plata u oro, de forma irregular y asimétrica, acuñadas en varios lugares del Imperio Español entre el siglo XVI y XVIII.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gouden of zilveren munten, onregelmatig van vorm en van ongelijke kwaliteit, die tussen de 16e en de 18e eeuw in verscheidene delen van het Spaanse Rijk werden gebruikt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
